S3 is a ... Key / value store for objects
Great for bigger objects, not so great for many small objects
serverless, scales infinitely, max object size is 5TB, versioning capability
Tires: S3 standard, S3 IA, S3 intelligent, S3 Glacier + Lifecycle policies
features: Versioning, Replication, MFA-Delete, access Logs
Security: IAM, Bucket policies, ACL, Access Points, Object Lambda, CORS, Object/vault lock
encryption: SSE-S3, SS3-KMS, SSE-C, client-side, TLS in transit, Default encryption
Batch operations on objects using S3 bactch, listing files using S3 inventory
Performance: multi-party upload, S3 transfer acceleration, S3 select
Automation: S3 Event Notifications (SQS, SNS, Lambda, EventBridge)
Use cases: static files, key value store for big files, website hosting
